-- Gerry Weber to Open Up to 80 Clothes Stores This Year, Welt Says
-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 2013-02-16T13:09:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-16/gerry-weber-to-open-up-to-80-clothes-stores-this-year-welt-says.html
German clothier  Gerry Weber
International AG  plans to open as many as 80 new stores, mainly
in Europe, Turkey and the U.S., this year,  Die Welt  said in a
pre-release, citing  owner  Gerry Weber.  Sales growth this year will mainly come from the new
openings, the newspaper cited Weber as saying.  “We can’t detect a crisis and continue to have a very
large potential for growth,” said Weber, according to Die Welt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
